					<description><![CDATA[Thank you... from someone who didn&#039;t know where to start making positive and lasting changes.

In my little writer&#039;s group I was asked what primary resolution I would make this year and how I would attain it. There were so many needs tugging at me I didn&#039;t know where to start. Because of my husband&#039;s hospital stay I started with nutrition. I gathered healthy new recipes I downloaded from the internet.  I am trying them out one by one. I am saving those we like in a three-ring binder that will eventually become my go-to cook book.

My 1% principle involves planning, shopping, preparation, cooking, serving and cleanup. Eventually this process will relieve stress and make the process more enjoyable.

My husband being in the hospital 6 days over Christmas with blood clots and heart/lung disease gave me the impetus. Eating there for so long changed my husband&#039;s eating habits. I jumped on it!  Praise the Lord!

Now I just have to remember the 1% principle.  Thank you for your wise coaching and generosity.  I am saving the articles as PDFs.   They are so encouraging! (I could write my New Year&#039;s resolution now. Ha!)

Sarah]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Thank you&#8230; from someone who didn&#8217;t know where to start making positive and lasting changes.</p>
<p>In my little writer&#8217;s group I was asked what primary resolution I would make this year and how I would attain it. There were so many needs tugging at me I didn&#8217;t know where to start. Because of my husband&#8217;s hospital stay I started with nutrition. I gathered healthy new recipes I downloaded from the internet.  I am trying them out one by one. I am saving those we like in a three-ring binder that will eventually become my go-to cook book.</p>
<p>My 1% principle involves planning, shopping, preparation, cooking, serving and cleanup. Eventually this process will relieve stress and make the process more enjoyable.</p>
<p>My husband being in the hospital 6 days over Christmas with blood clots and heart/lung disease gave me the impetus. Eating there for so long changed my husband&#8217;s eating habits. I jumped on it!  Praise the Lord!</p>
<p>Now I just have to remember the 1% principle.  Thank you for your wise coaching and generosity.  I am saving the articles as PDFs.   They are so encouraging! (I could write my New Year&#8217;s resolution now. Ha!)</p>
<p>Sarah</p>
