		By: Beth Anne		</title>
		<link>https://jamesclear.vercel.app/habits-fail#comment-13990</link>

		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Beth Anne]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 07 Jan 2015 15:55:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://jamesclear-com.uar9g7bv-liquidwebsites.com/?p=6424#comment-13990</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jamesclear.vercel.app/habits-fail#comment-13979&quot;&gt;Ruth Cooke&lt;/a&gt;.

Great advice here, James, and it makes perfect sense!  We all think we have to go big or go home... but what ends up happening is that we just go home.  Like the resolution to lose 50 pounds stat!  We obsess over calories and exercise for 2 hours/day for a week, then we&#039;re so burnt out we can&#039;t bring ourselves to try again.  

This year, I want exercise to be a built-in habit for me.  So I&#039;m committed to exercising every single day.  I set my goal at 20 minutes per day (although now I&#039;m wishing I would have just said 5 minutes and built on that....)  Some days I lift weights, other days I go for a run, but every day I know it must be done, and since I&#039;m not also trying to eat healthier, lose tons of pounds, or anything else, it&#039;s not so hard to do it.  It&#039;s not overwhelming, and I can&#039;t wait to see how great I&#039;ll feel by the end of the year when daily exercise has become an ingrained habit.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://jamesclear.vercel.app/habits-fail#comment-13979">Ruth Cooke</a>.</p>
<p>Great advice here, James, and it makes perfect sense!  We all think we have to go big or go home&#8230; but what ends up happening is that we just go home.  Like the resolution to lose 50 pounds stat!  We obsess over calories and exercise for 2 hours/day for a week, then we&#8217;re so burnt out we can&#8217;t bring ourselves to try again.  </p>
<p>This year, I want exercise to be a built-in habit for me.  So I&#8217;m committed to exercising every single day.  I set my goal at 20 minutes per day (although now I&#8217;m wishing I would have just said 5 minutes and built on that&#8230;.)  Some days I lift weights, other days I go for a run, but every day I know it must be done, and since I&#8217;m not also trying to eat healthier, lose tons of pounds, or anything else, it&#8217;s not so hard to do it.  It&#8217;s not overwhelming, and I can&#8217;t wait to see how great I&#8217;ll feel by the end of the year when daily exercise has become an ingrained habit.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
