					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jamesclear.vercel.app/habits-fail#comment-13966&quot;&gt;Bruce Harpham&lt;/a&gt;.

Don&#039;t use an &quot;empty number&quot; to track your success. Yes, email subscibers is an indicator for success, but no guarantee.

If you want to get rich, being a follower is enough. Following guides and following blueprints will do the trick. But if you want to move something you need to be a student. You have to think yourself.

Choose a number that gives you peace of mind. That could be having 200$ in your pocket at all times. That could be having 10k in the bank. That could be having your own house. That could be having 50 comments on each of your blogposts. That could be anything weird.

Don&#039;t try to sell your soul to make money, just to buy your soul back in the end.

You can use popups, selling psychology, 5 offers to join an email-list on every page, or whatever &quot;experts&quot; tell you to do. But you always have to ask the question: Do i want others do this to me?

Yes i&#039;m drunk. Yes this is going offtopic. Yes this is weird. But posting this gives me peace of mind.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://jamesclear.vercel.app/habits-fail#comment-13966">Bruce Harpham</a>.</p>
<p>Don&#8217;t use an &#8220;empty number&#8221; to track your success. Yes, email subscibers is an indicator for success, but no guarantee.</p>
<p>If you want to get rich, being a follower is enough. Following guides and following blueprints will do the trick. But if you want to move something you need to be a student. You have to think yourself.</p>
<p>Choose a number that gives you peace of mind. That could be having 200$ in your pocket at all times. That could be having 10k in the bank. That could be having your own house. That could be having 50 comments on each of your blogposts. That could be anything weird.</p>
<p>Don&#8217;t try to sell your soul to make money, just to buy your soul back in the end.</p>
<p>You can use popups, selling psychology, 5 offers to join an email-list on every page, or whatever &#8220;experts&#8221; tell you to do. But you always have to ask the question: Do i want others do this to me?</p>
<p>Yes i&#8217;m drunk. Yes this is going offtopic. Yes this is weird. But posting this gives me peace of mind.</p>
